TERRAFORM

Create IAM user with default settings
create users group
add the created user in user group and add "AdministratorAccess" in attach policies
click on user and go to security credentials
create access key 
select CLI
copy the Access Key and Secret Key on notepad 
then go EC2 instance 
click on launch instance
and look for AMI ID 
copy the AMI ID in notepad
and check the server "us-east-1"
open vs code and make a main.tf file
paste this code

provider "aws" {
  access_key = ""
  secret_key = ""
  region = "us-east-1"
}

resource "aws_instance" "xie_instance" {
  ami = "AMI"
  instance_type = "t3.micro"
  tags = {
    Name = "xie_instance"
  }
}

enter the details pasted on notepad (Access key, secret key, AMI ID)
then run commands in vscode terminal 
>terraform init
>terraform plan
>terraform apply
if error occurs change the instance type in code from "t3.micro" to "t2.micro".
>terraform destroy
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Kubernets

go to EC2
launch instance (ubuntu 22.04, t3.small)
make key pair
select RSA and .pem
in network settings click on edit
click on "add security group rule"
in port range "8080"
click on source and select "0.0.0.0/0"
launch instance
go to instances and select and click on connect
now paste the following commands

>sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get upgradeÃ‚ -y
>sudo apt-get install docker.io -y
>sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
>newgrp docker
>curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
>sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube
>minikube start
>minikube status
